{
  "id": "jsonbored_awesome-claude_522",
  "repo_name": "jsonbored/awesome-claude",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/jsonbored/awesome-claude",
  "base_commit": "80047855f804a5826a239cfe951326f4603aa68f",
  "pr_number": 522,
  "issue_number": 521,
  "issue_title": "fix(mcp): search_duplicate_entries misses URL variants and second candidate URLs",
  "issue_body": "## Goal\n\nMake the MCP `search_duplicate_entries` and `review_submission_draft` tools surface a duplicate match whenever a submitter's URL resolves to the same canonical resource as any source URL on any indexed entry \u2014 across trailing-slash variants, `www.` prefixes, `#hash` fragments, `utm_*`/affiliate query params, the secondary URL the caller's `||` chain currently drops, and the additional entry-URL fields (`downloadUrl`, `websiteUrl`, `githubUrl`, `trustSignals.sourceUrls`) the current helper omits.\n\n## Why this matters\n\n`packages/mcp/src/submissions.js` exposes two duplicate-detection surfaces:\n\n- `searchDuplicateEntries(entries, args)` is the engine behind the `search_duplicate_entries` MCP tool, which contributors and downstream agents use *before* opening a submission issue.\n- `reviewSubmissionDraftFromSpec(spec, args, entries)` calls `searchDuplicateEntries` from inside the `review_submission_draft` MCP tool to surface duplicates as part of the review payload.\n\nBoth surfaces are designed to stop low-quality / duplicate submissions before they become GitHub issues a maintainer has to triage. They currently miss obvious duplicates in three independent ways:\n\n1. **No URL normalization.** `entrySourceUrls` runs raw `normalizeText` (lowercase + trim) over the entry's URL fields and `searchDuplicateEntries` does a string `.includes(sourceUrl)`. A submitter typing `https://github.com/domdomegg/airtable-mcp-server/` (trailing slash) against an indexed entry whose `repoUrl === https://github.com/domdomegg/airtable-mcp-server` (no slash) gets `\"No obvious registry duplicate found in the generated search index.\"` Same for `www.` prefix, `#fragment`, `utm_*` tracking params, mixed case in scheme/host. Affiliate-tag stripping already exists elsewhere in the same file (for the affiliate URL guard), so this is a known shape \u2014 just not applied on the duplicate-detection path.\n\n2. **Only the first non-empty candidate URL is forwarded.** `reviewSubmissionDraftFromSpec` builds `sourceUrl` with `validation.normalized.github_url || validation.normalized.docs_url || validation.normalized.source_url`. If the submission carries both `github_url` AND `docs_url`, only `github_url` is ever checked against indexed entries; the `docs_url` half is dropped. Even if `searchDuplicateEntries` is upgraded, a submitter who supplies `docs_url` matching an existing entry's `documentationUrl` is only protected if they also leave `github_url` empty.\n\n3. **Indexed entries have URL fields the helper doesn't read.** `entrySourceUrls` reads `documentationUrl, repoUrl, url, canonicalUrl, llmsUrl, apiUrl`. It does not read `downloadUrl`, `websiteUrl`, `githubUrl`, or the `trustSignals.sourceUrls` array. Entries that carry any of those (e.g. a download-only artifact entry whose only external URL lives on `downloadUrl`) are unmatchable against a submitter's URL of any shape.\n\nThe fix is the canonical \"extract a normalize helper, route every comparison through it, broaden the URL-collection list\" pattern recently shipped here (PR #505 `fix(api): reject mismatched community signal targets`; PR #506 `fix(security): redact split CLI flag secrets` \u2014 both `fix(<scope>):` titles, both added small focused helpers and migrated the relevant call sites in a single PR). No design change, no public response-shape change: today's `reasons: [\"source_url\"]` payload stays exactly the same; the fix only changes which `sourceUrl` values produce that match.\n\n## Current behavior\n\n```js\n// packages/mcp/src/submissions.js (~L797-L808)\nfunction entrySourceUrls(entry) {\n  return [\n    entry.documentationUrl,\n    entry.repoUrl,\n    entry.url,\n    entry.canonicalUrl,\n    entry.llmsUrl,\n    entry.apiUrl,\n  ]\n    .map(normalizeText)   // lowercase + trim only \u2014 no URL normalization\n    .filter(Boolean);\n}\n\n// (~L829 inside searchDuplicateEntries)\nif (sourceUrl && entrySourceUrls(entry).includes(sourceUrl)) {\n  reasons.push(\"source_url\");\n}\n\n// (~L754-L758 inside reviewSubmissionDraftFromSpec)\nsourceUrl:\n  validation.normalized.github_url ||\n  validation.normalized.docs_url ||\n  validation.normalized.source_url,\n```\n\nEffect: `search_duplicate_entries` and `review_submission_draft` silently miss any duplicate where the submitter's URL differs from the indexed URL by a trailing slash, `www.` prefix, `#hash`, `utm_*` query param, or scheme/host case \u2014 or any duplicate whose only matching URL lives on `downloadUrl`/`websiteUrl`/`trustSignals.sourceUrls`. The downstream submission then reaches the maintainer queue as a \"novel\" submission for review.\n\n## Desired behavior\n\nFour new private helpers in the same file:\n\n- `normalizeSubmissionUrlForMatch(value)` \u2014 parses the URL with the `URL` constructor; lowercases scheme and hostname; strips a leading `www.`; drops the `#hash` fragment; drops `utm_*` and affiliate-tag query params (reusing the affiliate-key set already in this file); strips trailing `/` on a non-root path; returns `\"\"` on parse failure (so unparseable strings simply don't match anything).\n- `collectEntrySourceUrls(entry)` \u2014 returns a `Set<string>` of normalized URLs across `documentationUrl, repoUrl, githubUrl, websiteUrl, downloadUrl, url, canonicalUrl, llmsUrl, apiUrl` plus any strings in `entry.trustSignals?.sourceUrls`. Each URL is passed through `normalizeSubmissionUrlForMatch` before adding.\n- `collectSubmissionCandidateUrls(args)` \u2014 accepts the duplicate-search args shape and returns a deduped `Set<string>` of normalized candidate URLs: the scalar `args.sourceUrl`, plus any `args.sourceUrls` array, plus the fielded `args.githubUrl` / `args.docsUrl` / `args.downloadUrl` / `args.websiteUrl` (so callers can supply multiple candidates without `||`-chaining).\n- `findOverlappingSourceUrl(entryUrls, candidateUrls)` \u2014 returns the first overlapping normalized URL from the two Sets, or `\"\"`. Used both as the predicate that decides whether to push `\"source_url\"` into `reasons`, and (optionally) as the value that lets the caller surface *which* URL matched.\n\n`searchDuplicateEntries`'s `sourceUrl` branch is rewritten to call `collectSubmissionCandidateUrls(args)` once and `collectEntrySourceUrls(entry)` per candidate entry, then `findOverlappingSourceUrl(...)` to decide the `source_url` reason. `reviewSubmissionDraftFromSpec`'s `duplicateArgs` forwards a normalized + deduped `sourceUrls` array (built from `validation.normalized.github_url`, `docs_url`, `source_url`, `download_url`, `website_url`) instead of a `||`-chained single `sourceUrl`. The existing slug/title/brand_domain matches and reasons are untouched. The MCP response shape (`reasons: string[]`) is unchanged.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `packages/mcp/src/submissions.js` \u2014 add 4 helpers; replace `entrySourceUrls` with `collectEntrySourceUrls`; rewrite the `sourceUrl` branch of `searchDuplicateEntries`; rewrite `duplicateArgs` in `reviewSubmissionDraftFromSpec`.\n- `packages/mcp/src/submissions.d.ts` \u2014 extend the public `searchDuplicateEntries` args shape to include the new `sourceUrls?: string[]` plus the fielded URL fields so TS consumers can call the broader API.\n- `tests/mcp-server.test.ts` \u2014 extend the existing `search_duplicate_entries` test to cover a trailing-slash variant + a `docs_url`-only variant.\n- `tests/mcp-submission-duplicate-urls.test.ts` (new) \u2014 direct unit tests against `searchDuplicateEntries`/`collectEntrySourceUrls`/`normalizeSubmissionUrlForMatch` for the four normalization classes.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- The website-side `apps/web/src/lib/submission-preflight.ts` \u2014 that surface is the subject of maintainer-filed issue #428 (FRONTEND, web `/submit` UX, near-match guidance). This fix is MCP-tool correctness on exact-after-normalization matches; the two compose.\n- `searchDuplicateEntries`'s slug/title/brand_domain branches \u2014 unchanged in this fix.\n- Adding near-match / fuzzy-title scoring \u2014 explicitly the goal of #428.\n- Validation-spec changes (`validateAgainstSpec`) \u2014 unchanged.\n- API contracts for any HTTP route \u2014 unchanged (this is MCP-only; no OpenAPI regen needed).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- PR includes `Closes #<issue>`.\n- `normalizeSubmissionUrlForMatch(\"https://www.GitHub.com/foo/bar/#abc?utm_source=x\")` returns `\"https://github.com/foo/bar\"`.\n- `normalizeSubmissionUrlForMatch(\"not-a-url\")` returns `\"\"`.\n- `collectEntrySourceUrls(entry)` includes normalized URLs from `documentationUrl, repoUrl, githubUrl, websiteUrl, downloadUrl, url, canonicalUrl, llmsUrl, apiUrl, trustSignals.sourceUrls`.\n- `searchDuplicateEntries(entries, { sourceUrl: \"<trailing-slash variant>\" })` returns `reasons: [\"source_url\"]` against an indexed entry that carries the no-slash variant on any source-URL field.\n- `searchDuplicateEntries(entries, { sourceUrls: [...] })` accepts an array and matches any entry that overlaps with any candidate.\n- `reviewSubmissionDraftFromSpec` forwards both `github_url` and `docs_url` (and `source_url`, `download_url`, `website_url`) when the submission carries multiple URLs; the duplicate match no longer depends on which URL field was filled first.\n- Existing slug/title/brand_domain duplicate detection is unchanged in behavior.\n- `pnpm exec vitest run tests/mcp-server.test.ts tests/mcp-submission-duplicate-urls.test.ts` passes.\n- `pnpm test:mcp` (mcp-server + mcp-cli) passes.\n- `pnpm type-check` passes.\n\n## Quality evidence required in the PR\n\n- No visual impact (MCP-only fix; no UI / page changes).\n- PR description lists the three independent gaps closed (no normalization, dropped-second-URL, missing entry fields) and the four new helpers, with the file:line of each callsite migrated.\n- Before/after for one representative case: a trailing-slash variant currently returns `count: 0`; after the fix, returns `reasons: [\"source_url\"]`.\n- Backward-compatibility note: the public response shape is unchanged; existing exact-match duplicates still match; only the previously-missed normalized matches and the previously-dropped second-URL candidates produce additional matches.\n\n## Validation\n\n```\npnpm install\npnpm exec vitest run tests/mcp-server.test.ts tests/mcp-submission-duplicate-urls.test.ts\npnpm test:mcp\npnpm type-check\ngit diff --check\n```\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-28T23:30:49.000Z",
